Package org.jamplate.model

A package that specifies that primary components of a processor that uses the jamplate-style processing.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Compilation
    A compilation is a structure holding the variables for a single compilation unit (like a file).
    Document
    An interface that abstracts the functionality required to deal with source-code files.
    Environment
    The environment is a unit holding all the data, managers and variables about a single process.
    Instruction
    An instruction is a function that executes depending on the state of the environment and memory given to it but does not have a state itself.
    Value
    The value function is a function that evaluates to a value depending on the state of the memory given to it.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Frame
    An isolated part in the memory.
    Memory
    The memory is a structure that saves the variables at the runtime.
    Reference
    A source reference is a component that points to a document or a fragment of it.
    Sketch
    A class that holds the thoughts about a syntax or runtime component.
    Tree
    A tree is a point in a background structure of sketches that hold the variables of a runtime or a text component.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Dominance
    An enumeration of how dominant a relation is over another relation.
    Intersection
    An enumeration of possible intersections between sources.
    Relation
    An enumeration of the possible directions to the relatives of a source.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    CompileException
    An exception indicating a failure while compiling.
    DocumentNotFoundException
    An exception that indicates that an attempt to read an unreadable document occurred.
    ExecutionException
    An exception indicating failure on executing an instruction.
    IllegalTreeException
    An exception indicating that an illegal tree was provided.
    TreeClashException
    An exception to indicate that a provided tree is clashing with another tree and the operation cannot continue because of that.
    TreeOutOfBoundsException
    An exception to indicate that a provided tree is out of the expected bounds.
    TreeTakeoverException
    This exception is a more specific exception of the TreeClashException.
  • Error Summary 
    Error Description
    DocumentNotFoundError
    An unchecked throwable equivalent to DocumentNotFoundError.

Package org.jamplate.model Description

A package that specifies that primary components of a processor that uses the jamplate-style processing.

Enums
  • Relation
    An enumeration representing a relation between two trees.
  • Dominance
    An enumeration representing how dominance a tree over another.
  • Intersection
    An enumeration representing how a tree intersect with another.

Constant Components:
  • Document
    A constant that represents a source unit.
  • Reference
    A constant that represents a range (area).

Building Components:
  • Tree
    An absolute building block that reserves an area in a document.
    • Its Document.
    • Its Reference.
    • The Trees around it.
    • A Sketch representing the tree.
  • Sketch
    A relative building block that represent its data without a position.
    • Its origin Tree.
    • Its component Sketchs.
    • Additional meta data.

Built Components:
  • Value
    A built component that can be evaluated into a string.
  • Instruction
    A built component that can be executed.
    • Its origin Tree.

Environment Components:
  • Environment
    A fixed structure that holds the variables of a whole process.
    • A Diagnostic Manager.
    • A set of Compilations.
    • Additional meta data.
  • Compilation
    A fixed structure that holds the variables of a whole document.
    • The represented Document.
    • A root Tree.
    • A compiled Instruction.
    • Additional meta data.

Volatile Components:
  • Frame
    A highly stateful mutable structure that can store and release values/data in a stack and heap fashion.
  • The host Instruction.
  • A stack of values.
  • A heap of values.
  • Memory
    A highly stateful mutable structure that can store and release frames in a stack fashion.
    • A stack of Frames.
    • A console.

Functions:
  • Initializer
    A function that initializes a Document into an Environment.
  • Parser
    A function tries to constructs a set of Trees from a Tree.
  • Analyzer
    A function that analyzes and modifies a Tree.
  • Compiler
    A function tires to construct an Instruction from a Tree.
  • Processor
    An function that processes a Compilation.
Since:
0.2.0 ~2021.01.17
Version:
0.2.0
Author:
LSafer
